      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Martin Parks Burks was the deputy sheriff of Bedford
         County, Virginia.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Chiefly accounts, receipts and business letters of Martin
         P. Burks, 1798-1866, including records while he was deputy
         sheriff of Bedford County, Virginia.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <arrangement>
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>Collection is arranged chronologically.</p>
         </arrangement>
         <arrangement>
            <head>Organization</head>
            <p>The collection has been broken down into three series.
            Series 1 are the accounts of Thomas Turpin, Series 2 are
            the papers relating to the sheriff's office of Bedford
            County, and Series 3 are the personal papers of Martin P.
            Burks.</p>
         </arrangement>
      </arrangement>
